title: Meek Mill Previews Music From "DC4.5" Mixtape
text:
Home > Music > Meek Mill Previews Music From "DC4.5" Mixtape Meek Mill Previews Music From "DC4.5" Mixtape 14 4 Posted by Shaun M , Jan 16, 2017 at 04:06pm Meek Mill shared a snippet from upcoming "DC 4.5" mixtape on Instagram. 
A while back, Meek Mill shared some cover art from his upcoming mixtape "DC4.5," a follow-up to his successful "DC4" project that climbed the Billboard charts last fall. Sunday night, the Philly rapper shared some new music on Instagram that sounded like fire. In the video, Meek and an associate are seen blasting a snippet from the new tape. A video posted by Meek Mill (@meekmill) on Jan 16, 2017 at 12:04am PST 
Despite the bad publicity Meek incurred in recent weeks -- the breakup with Nicki Minaj , the boxing challenge to Drake taken up by Safaree, the icy fall caught on video -- "DC4.5" remains on most hip hop fans' radar due to the success of "DC4." The project went all the way up to the third position on Billboard 200 charts. Meek announced its follow-up merely a week after it was released. No doubt, he wants to build on that good momentum for a change. < class="robots-nocontent" rel=""> Jan 16, 2017 at 04:06pm 2.2K Views
